name: Edition 3/22 tarot card - The High Priestess
description:
Size: 2362 x 4725 px
This edition card will be released every 4 days.

It's time to trust your own instincts and listen to your own intuition! The High Priestess will send her signs to you through the universe, or even through your dreams. So, pay attention to every symbol from her.

The High Priestess is a nun who is crowned with the Papal Tiara and wears a plain blue robe. In her hands, there is a scroll that bears the letters TORAH, which means divine law. She also has a crescent moon on her feet.

She is seated between the 'B' (Boaz) and 'J' (Jachin) pillars to brings balance, because these pillars represent the opposites. Behind her, there is embroidery with palm leaf (for male) and pomegranate (for female) ornaments. Meanwhile, the ocean represents her intuitive emotions.

The High Priestess is numbered 2 in the Major Arcana, a very empathetic person who exactly knows how you are feeling and has wisdom inside that reflects when she will give you advice.
